{
  "text": ", which is precisely related to the lattice factor appearing in the Calabrese-Cardy lattice formula for the spatial entanglement entropy of a CFT [CITATION_1] . At a cutoff momentum of k 0 = \u03c0 2 , we recover the exact continuum value for a global boost on the edge. When k 0 \u223c 0, \u03c0, we expect the lattice effects to be maximal because we are close to the limit of an empty or fully filled edge band respectively, and the dispersion becomes non-chiral. The fact that we have found lattice modifications to the connection between entanglement and gravity may give hints about how to properly discuss lattice regularizations of gravitational anomalies, although we leave that to future work.",
